Q: A rectangular piece of 150 sq m has a length which is 1m more than the 4 times the breadth. What is the perimeter of the piece?
Options: (a) 60 m (b) 61 m (c) 62 m (d) 63 m (e) 64 m
A:
 Let the breadth be x. Then the length is 4x + 1. The area is 150, so x(4x + 1) = 150. 4x^2 + x - 150 = 0. (4x + 15)(x - 10) = 0. x = 10, x = -15/4. Since x is the breadth, x = 10. The length is 4x + 1 = 41. The perimeter is 2(10 + 41) = 102. So the answer is (e).

