Q: Jim filled his dog's bowl with dog food. Starting at 8:00 am, Jim's dog ate exactly once an hour, consuming exactly 1/3 of the dog food remaining in the bowl at each feeding session. Approximately, what percent of the original food was in the dog's bowl right before the dog began to eat at noon of the same day?
Options: (a) 20% (b) 25% (c) 30% (d) 35% (e) 40%
A:
 The dog ate 1/3 of the food at 9 am, 1/3 of the remaining food at 10 am, and 1/3 of the remaining food at 11 am. So the dog ate 1/3 + 2/3*1/3 + 1/3*2/3 = 1/3 + 2/9 + 4/27 = 1/3 + 2/9 + 8/81 = 27/81 + 18/81 + 8/81 = 53/81. So the dog ate 53/81 of the original food. The dog ate 53/81 of the original food, so the dog had 1 - 53/81 = 28/81 of the original food left. 28/81 is approximately 35%. So the answer is (d).

