Q: Anna is able to buy 5 more articles for $300 after the price of each article decreased by 15%. What is the new selling price of each article?
Options: (a) $8 (b) $10 (c) $13.6 (d) $22.9 (e) $40
A:
 Let the original price of each article be x. Then, the new price of each article is 0.85x. 5 articles cost 300, so 0.85x * 5 = 300. x = 300/4.25 = 60. So the new price of each article is 0.85 * 60 = 51. So the answer is (d).

