Q: Last year, a Home Appliance Store sold an average(arithmetic mean) of 42 microwave ovens per month. In the first 10 months of this year,the store has sold an average(arithmetic mean) of only 20 microwave ovens per month. What was the average number of microwave ovens sold per month during the entire 22 months period?
Options: (a) 21 (b) 30 (c) 31 (d) 32 (e) None of the above
A:
 The total number of microwave ovens sold in 22 months = 10 * 20 + 12 * 42 = 200 + 504 = 704. The average number of microwave ovens sold per month during the entire 22 months period = 704/22 = 32. So the answer is (d).

