Q: A club consists of members whose ages are in A.P. The common difference being 3 months. If the youngest member of the club is just 7 years old and the sum of the ages of all the members is 250, then number of members in the club are :
Options: (a) 18 (b) 20 (c) 25 (d) 26 (e) 27
A:
 Let the number of members be n. Then the sum of the ages of all the members is 7 + 10 + 13 +... + (7 + 3n - 3) = 250. This is an A.P. with first term 7 and last term 7 + 3n - 3. The sum of the terms of an A.P. is (n/2) * (first term + last term). So, (n/2) * (7 + 7 + 3n - 3) = 250. 7n/2 + 7 = 250. 7n/2 = 243. n = 18. So the number of members is 18. So the answer is (a).

