Q: Two ants are moving from their farms towards each other. Ant A is moving at a speed of 9 cm per hour and ant B is moving at a speed of 6 cm per hour. If the farms are 75 cm away from each other, what will be the distance (in cm) that ant A travels until meeting ant B?
Options: (a) 45 (b) 48 (c) 51 (d) 54 (e) 57
A:
 The distance between the two ants is 75 cm. The relative speed of the two ants is 9 + 6 = 15 cm per hour. So the time taken to meet is 75/15 = 5 hours. In 5 hours, ant A travels 9 * 5 = 45 cm. So the answer is (a).

